title: Roadmaster - Fortress [1980]
description: For their 4th album Roadmaster continued with shorter album-oriented rock songs, a number of them with a harder sound. After Hey World sold a decent number of copies, Mercury Records had high hopes for this album. It didn&#039;t sell well and the label dropped the band. Toby Myers ended up joining John Mellencamp&#039;s touring band while Michael Read and Rick Benick toured with Henry Lee Summer.
